# Go Service Conventions (apps/sim/)

## Stack
- Go 1.25, chi/v5 router, pgx/v5 PostgreSQL driver, godotenv
- Build: `make build` | Test: `make test` | Dev: `make watch` (air live reload)

## Package Structure
- `cmd/api/` — HTTP server entrypoint only
- `internal/server/` — HTTP routes, handlers, middleware (chi router)
- `internal/database/` — Postgres connection, health checks (pgx/sql.DB singleton)
- `internal/model/` — Domain types (Deal, SimulationRequest, Metric, YearlyValues)
- `internal/engine/` — Monte Carlo simulation engine (rng, distribution, copula)
- `internal/stats/` — Statistical aggregation (Welford, Histogram, Reservoir)

## Patterns to Follow

### HTTP Handlers
- Receiver methods on `*Server` struct: `func (s *Server) MyHandler(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)`
- Follow pattern in `apps/sim/internal/server/routes.go`

### Error Handling
- Validation: Explicit `Validate()` methods returning `error`
- Wrapping: `fmt.Errorf("context: %w", err)` for error context
- Fatal: `log.Fatal()` only for unrecoverable startup errors
- Follow pattern in `apps/sim/internal/model/simulation.go`

### Database
- pgx via database/sql stdlib adapter
- Singleton service with `Service` interface
- Connection DSN from env vars (`BLUEPRINT_DB_*`)
- Follow pattern in `apps/sim/internal/database/database.go`

### Config
- Environment variables loaded via `godotenv/autoload`
- Read with `os.Getenv()` at init time
- Env vars prefixed: `BLUEPRINT_DB_*`, `PORT`, `APP_ENV`

### Testing
- Table-driven tests with standard `testing.T`
- Manual assertions (no testify/assert)
- Integration tests with `testcontainers-go` for Postgres
- HTTP tests with `httptest.NewServer`
- Follow pattern in `apps/sim/internal/model/model_test.go`

### Naming
- Files: lowercase with underscores (`database.go`, `routes_test.go`)
- Packages: lowercase, single word (`server`, `database`, `model`)
- Types: PascalCase (`Server`, `Deal`, `SimulationRequest`)
- Constants: PascalCase for exported, SCREAMING_SNAKE for numeric limits
- Interfaces: suffix with `-Service` (`Service` interface)

## Anti-Patterns
- Do NOT use gin, fiber, or echo — this project uses chi
- Do NOT use gorm — this project uses pgx/stdlib
- Do NOT use testify — use standard assertions
- Do NOT add new direct dependencies without justification
